metadata.name: So Close, So Far
metadata.description:
Look around the world
that in the bedclothes of his broken sleep
It is alien to itself.

And look at us,
Awake
that we are conscious of our own sorrow;

Angry and aggressive
We guard our bitter sorrow,
We are the sullen guardians of our suffering
so that it does not make a mistake from the black frame of the task that we have drawn around it.

And look at the world
the world
In the innocent slumber of its sleep;
What a stranger to himself!

The month passes
At the end of its cold circuit.

We are left and
The day will not come.
A.Bamdad
